"title\":\"Models | Prisma Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://www.prisma.io/docs/orm/prisma-schema/data-model/models\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Prisma and UNIQUE DEFERRABLE constraints:\n\n## Current Status\n\nUnique constraints are enforced during each statement in a database operation by default. However, it would be useful to defer this enforcement to the end of the full transaction in some cases where values are getting \"shifted\" and may be temporarily duplicated.\n\n## Feature Request Status\n\nThis is possible in PostgreSQL and possibly other databases. The feature request is to allow DEFERRED options to be defined in the Prisma schema, alongside the @unique declarations. This will allow Prisma to keep the DEFERRED options in sync with the schema AND the database.\n\n## Current Limitations\n\nPrisma does not currently support declaring DEFERRABLE constraints natively in the schema. It can currently be done directly in the database manually but will be overwritten when the schema is deployed with Migrate.\n\n## Workarounds\n\nThe documented workaround involves:\n1. Dropping the @unique constraint from the Prisma schema and migrating it to the database. Manually altering the constraint in the database directly with custom SQL to add the deferrals. Using prisma db pull to \"rediscover\" the unique constraint so it would be enforced in the code/typings.\n\nHowever, this will be overwritten if prisma migrate dev for example is run in the future, so it's not a sustainable solution.\n\nThis appears to be an open feature request rather than a currently implemented feature in Prisma.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"4afbfb7e-1c6f-4db2-a64b-81beedc12dc3","timestamp":"2026-03-27T15:28:00.671Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Prisma UNIQUE DEFERRABLE constraint","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01SuXaEjdQywgwuPpjyVzY3K","content":[{"title":"Allow deferral of unique constraints using definitions in Prisma schema · Issue #8807 · prisma/prisma","url":"https://github.com/prisma/prisma/issues/8807"},{"title":"Allow deferral of unique constraints using definitions in Prisma schema · Issue #8806 · prisma/prisma","url":"https://github.com/prisma/prisma/issues/8806"},{"title":"Allow deferral of unique constraints using definitions in Prisma schema","url":"https://lightrun.com/answers/prisma-prisma-allow-deferral-of-unique-constraints-using-definitions-in-prisma-schema"},{"title":"Defer @@unique constraint until end of transaction · prisma/prisma · Discussion #8789","url":"https://github.com/prisma/prisma/discussions/8789"},{"title":"Working with compound IDs and unique constraints (Concepts) | Prisma Documentation","url":"https://www.prisma.io/docs/orm/prisma-client/special-fields-and-types/working-with-composite-ids-and-constraints"},{"title":"Issue with Unique Constraint in Prisma Schema · prisma/prisma · Discussion #22815","url":"https://github.com/prisma/prisma/discussions/22815"},{"title":"PR for deferrable relation support in schema · prisma/prisma · Discussion #14064","url":"https://github.com/prisma/prisma/discussions/14064"},{"title":"How To Handle Prisma Unique Constraints with a Friendly Error - Show & Tell - RedwoodJS Community","url":"https://community.redwoodjs.com/t/how-to-handle-prisma-unique-constraints-with-a-friendly-error/4117"},{"title":"Correctness and Constraints | Data Modeling | Prisma's Data Guide","url":"https://www.prisma.io/dataguide/datamodeling/correctness-constraints"},{"title":"Models | Prisma Documentation","url":"https://www.prisma.io/docs/orm/prisma-schema/data-model/models"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found about Prisma and UNIQUE DEFERRABLE constraints:\n\n## Current Status\n\nUnique constraints are enforced during each statement in a database operation by default. However, it would be useful to defer this enforcement to the end of the full transaction in some cases where values are getting \"shifted\" and may be temporarily duplicated.\n\n## Feature Request Status\n\nThis is possible in PostgreSQL and possibly other databases. The feature request is to allow DEFERRED options to be defined in the Prisma schema, alongside the @unique declarations. This will allow Prisma to keep the DEFERRED options in sync with the schema AND the database.\n\n## Current Limitations\n\nPrisma does not currently support declaring DEFERRABLE constraints natively in the schema. It can currently be done directly in the database manually but will be overwritten when the schema is deployed with Migrate.\n\n## Workarounds\n\nThe documented workaround involves:\n1. Dropping the @unique constraint from the Prisma schema and migrating it to the database. Manually altering the constraint in the database directly with custom SQL to add the deferrals. Using prisma db pull to \"rediscover\" the unique constraint so it would be enforced in the code/typings.\n\nHowever, this will be overwritten if prisma migrate dev for example is run in the future, so it's not a sustainable solution.\n\nThis appears to be an open feature request rather than a currently implemented feature in Prisma."],"durationSeconds":7.034807541999966},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"cf4dc099-f7d8-43ca-8acf-08ba32e2bc9c","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/haru/ghq/github.com/harusame0616/ijuku","sessionId":"e31a75d7-afc2-4fef-85d0-5463c85780d4","version":"2.1.84","gitBranch":"2","slug":"rippling-munching-crown"}
